recision) and missed barcodes (recall) for linear barcodes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some barcode types are naturally prone to false positives (e.g. MSI Plessey)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For those barcode types false positives can be drastically reduced (precision can be increased) by requiring that multiple scan-lines in the input scan to the same result."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, this stronger condition can lead to missed barcodes (lower recall)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Confirmation is avoided for barcode types, which are by design resistant to false positives, (e.g. Code128) to maximize recall."}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkonedconfirmationmode"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBarcodeFormatCode93Configuration/initWithRegexFilter:minimumSizeScore:addAdditionalQuietZone:minimum1DQuietZoneSize:minimumNumberOfRequiredFramesWithEqualRecognitionResult:oneDConfirmationMode:stripCheckDigits:minimumTextLength:maximumTextLength:enableOneDBlurScanner:":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"initWithRegexFilter:minimumSizeScore:addAdditionalQuietZone:minimum1DQuietZoneSize:minimumNumberOfRequiredFramesWithEqualRecognitionResult:oneDConfirmationMode:stripCheckDigits:minimumTextLength:maximumTextLength:enableOneDBlurScanner:","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBarcodeFormatCode93Configuration\/initWithRegexFilter:minimumSizeScore:addAdditionalQuietZone:minimum1DQuietZoneSize:minimumNumberOfRequiredFramesWithEqualRecognitionResult:oneDConfirmationMode:stripCheckDigits:minimumTextLength:maximumTextLength:enableOneDBlurScanner:","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbarcodeformatcode93configuration\/initwithregexfilter:minimumsizescore:addadditionalquietzone:minimum1dquietzonesize:minimumnumberofrequiredframeswithequalrecognit